---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import site from '../../site.config.json';
const c = site.colours;
---
<BaseLayout title="Printix vs PaperCut -- Cloud Print Management Comparison" description="Compare Printix and PaperCut cloud print management platforms. Architecture, deployment approach, and positioning for Australian organisations.">
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:800px">
      <p class="eyebrow">COMPARE</p>
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,42px);font-weight:800;margin-bottom:16px">Printix vs PaperCut</h1>
      <p class="muted" style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:40px">Printix and PaperCut are both established cloud print management platforms used by organisations worldwide. Both offer serverless printing, cloud-based administration, secure print release, and broad device support. The differences lie in product architecture, deployment philosophy, and how each platform approaches feature packaging and pricing.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:16px">Printix at a glance</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Printix is a cloud-native print management platform designed from the ground up as a single SaaS product. All features are included at every pricing tier, with volume-based discounts determined by user count. Printix emphasises simplified deployment with no on-premise server infrastructure required, cloud-based driver management, and built-in support for remote and hybrid printing without VPN configuration.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Secure print release is available via mobile app, QR code, NFC, or ID badge. The management interface is a cloud web dashboard, and identity integration supports Entra ID, Google Workspace, Okta, and OneLogin. Platform support covers Windows, Mac, Chromebook, iOS, and Android.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:16px">PaperCut at a glance</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">PaperCut offers a range of print management products spanning cloud-native and self-hosted deployment models. PaperCut Hive is a cloud-native, serverless SaaS solution with driverless printing, cloud administration, secure print release, and support for Entra ID and Google Workspace identity providers. PaperCut MF is a feature-rich, self-hosted platform available for on-premise or cloud-hosted server deployment, offering advanced reporting, granular policy controls, and deep integration with multifunction devices.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">This range gives organisations flexibility to choose a deployment model that matches their environment, from fully cloud-managed to self-hosted with maximum configuration control. PaperCut products support Windows, Mac, Linux, Chromebook, iOS, and Android devices.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:16px">Where each platform is typically preferred</h2>
      <div class="compare-cards">
        <div class="compare-card">
          <h3 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:12px;color:var(--brand)">Printix may suit organisations that</h3>
          <ul class="compare-list">
            <li>Want a single cloud-native product with all features included at every tier</li>
            <li>Prioritise removing on-premise print server infrastructure entirely</li>
            <li>Need straightforward remote and hybrid printing without VPN setup</li>
            <li>Prefer per-user subscription pricing with predictable costs</li>
            <li>Value rapid deployment and minimal ongoing IT administration</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-card">
          <h3 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:12px;color:var(--brand)">PaperCut may suit organisations that</h3>
          <ul class="compare-list">
            <li>Want flexibility to choose between cloud-native (Hive) or self-hosted (MF) deployment</li>
            <li>Require advanced reporting, granular policy controls, or deep MFD integration</li>
            <li>Have existing PaperCut deployments and invested infrastructure</li>
            <li>Need Linux server support or highly customised print workflows</li>
            <li>Prefer tiered product options with different feature sets at different price points</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:16px">Key considerations</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Both platforms offer cloud-based administration, secure print release, and identity provider integration. The primary distinction is architectural philosophy: Printix delivers all capabilities through a single cloud-native product, while PaperCut provides a portfolio of products (Hive, Pocket, MF, NG) designed for different organisational requirements and deployment preferences.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Pricing models differ: Printix uses per-user subscription pricing with all features included, while PaperCut pricing varies by product tier and typically uses per-device licensing for MF/NG or per-user pricing for Hive. Organisations should request current pricing from each vendor, as models and rates may change.</p>

      <p class="muted compare-disclaimer" style="font-size:13px;margin-top:32px;font-style:italic">This comparison is based on publicly available information and general product positioning as of March 2026. Features, capabilities, and pricing may vary depending on configuration, version, and deployment model. Verify current details directly with each vendor before making purchasing decisions.</p>
      <p class="muted compare-disclaimer" style="font-size:13px;margin-top:12px;font-style:italic">PaperCut is a registered trademark of PaperCut Software International Pty Ltd. This site is not affiliated with or endorsed by PaperCut. Printix is a product of Tungsten Automation.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section-pad section-dark" style="padding:60px 0">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:12px">Try Printix free for 30 days</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-bottom:24px">All features included. No credit card required.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap"><a href={site.hero.ctaPrimaryUrl} class="btn-primary">Start free trial</a><a href="/contact" class="btn-secondary" style="border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3);color:#fff">Request a quote</a></div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <style is:inline>
    .eyebrow{font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:var(--brand);letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:12px}
    .compare-cards{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:24px;margin-top:24px}
    .compare-card{background:var(--neutral);border-radius:12px;padding:28px}
    .compare-list{list-style:none;padding:0}
    .compare-list li{position:relative;padding-left:20px;font-size:15px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:8px}
    .compare-list li::before{content:'\2713';position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--brand);font-weight:700}
    @media(max-width:768px){.compare-cards{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
